               <head>Mir'at al-ahval-i jahan-numa</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mirʾāt al-aḥvāl-i jahān numā by Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ʿAlī ibn Muḥammad Bāqir al-Iṣfahānī al-mashhūr bi-al-Bihbahānī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010050 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85067899 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85112612" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3941-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="viaf_79488721">Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ʿAlī ibn Muḥammad Bāqir al-Iṣfahānī al-mashhūr bi-al-Bihbahānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_79488721" type="alt">احمد ابن محمّد على ابن محمّد باقر الاصفهانى المشهور بالبهبهانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21914">Mirʾāt al-aḥvāl-i jahān numā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21914">مرآۃ الاحوال جهان نما</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Incorrect title (f. 3r): <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Taz̲kirah-yi Mīrzā Muḥammad Bāqir Lāhawrī</term>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                           <term xml:lang="en">Autobiography</term>, beginning with biographical notices of prominent Shi'ite scholars related to the author: 1) <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_11844492" role="subject">Muḥammad Taqī</persName>, 2) <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_17071179" role="subject">Muḥammad Bāqir ibn Muḥammad Taqī</persName>, 3) <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7400" role="subject">Muḥammad Ṣaliḥ</persName>, 4) <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_314817693" role="subject">Muḥammad Bāqir ibn Muḥammad Akmal al-Bihbihānī</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Bears a <term xml:lang="en">dedication</term> to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7717" role="pat">Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān Bahādur Qājār</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Concludes (ff. 261r-321v) with a description of the world according to Copernicus, discussing China, the Pope (Pāpā), and royal dynasties of England from the Saxon Kingdoms to the Hanoverian, King George III ("the English are very pleased with him"), describing London, and terminating abruptly with a discussion on English laws (subsequent folios lost)</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
